{"user_message": {"title": "ADR 0004 — Money Display Formatter (formatMoney) — SHIPPED, merge gated on pre-existing lint", "content": "## ADR 0004 — Currency-aware money display formatter (`formatMoney`)\n\n**Decision:** Added `src/features/ledger/lib/format.ts` exporting `formatMoney(value, currency, locale?)` — the display-side pair to the ADR 0002/0003 money stack. Real code shipped, not just a plan.\n\n### Context\nThe ledger had `roundMoney` (ADR 0002) and `addMoney`/`subtractMoney` (ADR 0003) keeping the *stored* value canonical, but **no display primitive**. Ad-hoc `` `$${v}` `` / `toFixed(2)` hard-code the symbol and 2-decimal assumption (wrong for JPY/BHD and non-US locales) and can render a value that drifts from what's stored.\n\n### Decision\n- **`Intl.NumberFormat` (style:'currency')** drives symbol placement, grouping, and minor-unit precision — locale/currency-correct by construction (`$1,234.50`, `1.234,56 €`, `¥1,235`).\n- **`locale` defaults to `'en-US'`.**\n- **Normalized through `roundMoney` first** → display can never disagree with stored value by float drift; also normalizes `-0 → 0`.\n- **Fail-loud** reusing ADR 0003's `MoneyArithmeticError` (`not-finite` / `mixed-currency`); blank currency → `RangeError`.\n- Wired into the `features/ledger` barrel.\n\n### Consequences\n- One drift-free, currency- & locale-aware formatter; display provably consistent with stored value across ADR 0003 arithmetic.\n- Residual risk: exact strings are ICU-version-sensitive (UNVERIFIED across all deploy targets; the test runtime confirms expected output). No `Intl` instance caching yet — negligible at current volume.\n\n### Verification\n```chart\nTotal tests passing: 42\nNew format tests: 8\nArithmetic tests: 9\nRound tests: 13\nAmount tests: 12\n```\n- `npm test` → **42/42 pass** (incl. Reviewer check: `formatMoney(addMoney(0.1,0.2,'USD'),'USD') === \"$0.30\"`).\n- `tsc --noEmit` clean. `eslint` on changed files (format.ts, format.test.ts, index.ts) **clean**.\n- Test coverage: USD default-locale, EUR `de-DE` (comma decimal + €), JPY (0 minor units), negatives (incl. `-0`), very large values, NaN/Infinity rejection, mixed-currency rejection, end-to-end arithmetic consistency.\n\n### ⚠️ Release gate: MERGE BLOCKED (not all-green)\nFull-repo `eslint .` fails with **1 error** — but it is **pre-existing and unrelated** to this change:\n```\nsrc/app/page.tsx:9:11  @next/next/no-html-link-for-pages\n  Do not use an  element to navigate to '/'. Use  from next/link.\n```\nThis file is untouched by this work (last modified by commit `d5f670c`, brand assets). My three changed files lint clean. Per the explicit release rule — *“if lint fails on the post-merge state, do NOT merge, escalate via manual_review”* — **I did not merge.** Fixing `page.tsx` is outside ledger scope (scoped as Task 6, 1pt) and flagged for human decision below.\n\n### Task breakdown (8 pts — 7 delivered, 1 blocking)\n1. `formatMoney` + `Intl` currency formatting (default `en-US`) — **2 pts** ✅\n2. Normalize through `roundMoney` (canonical value + `-0→0`) — **1 pt** ✅\n3. Fail-loud rejection via `MoneyArithmeticError` — **1 pt** ✅\n4. Unit tests (6 required + Reviewer check) — **2 pts** ✅\n5. Barrel export — **1 pt** ✅\n6. Resolve pre-existing `page.tsx` lint error (`` → `next/link`) so the gate is all-green — **1 pt** ⛔ blocked/escalated\n\nADR published at `docs/adr/0004-money-display-formatter.md`.", "content_type": "warning", "priority": "high"}}

